To run Playwright test runner in the "Executor" of `project.json`, you'll need to configure the executor to use the Playwright test command. Here's an example of how you can do it:

```json
{
  "executors": {
    "playwright": {
      "type": "shell",
      "command": "npx playwright test",
      "args": []
    }
  }
}
```

In this example:

* `playwright` is the name of the executor.
* `type` is set to `shell`, which means the command will be executed in a shell.
* `command` is set to `npx playwright test`, which runs the Playwright test command.
* `args` is an empty array, which means no additional arguments will be passed to the command.

Once you've configured the executor, you can run your Playwright tests using the following command:

```bash
nx run playwright
```

This will execute the Playwright test command using the `playwright` executor.

If you want to pass additional arguments to the Playwright test command, you can add them to the `args` array. For example:

```json
{
  "executors": {
    "playwright": {
      "type": "shell",
      "command": "npx playwright test",
      "args": [
        "--browser=chromium",
        "--headed"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

In this example, the `--browser=chromium` and `--headed` arguments will be passed to the Playwright test command.

Note that you can also use the `nx run` command with additional options to customize the test run. For example:

```bash
nx run playwright --browser=chromium --headed
```

This will override the `args` array in the `project.json` file and pass the specified arguments to the Playwright test command.

