```
The `java-websocket` library provides a basic WebSocket implementation, while `sockjs-client` and `stomp-client` provide the SockJS and STOMP protocol implementations, respectively.

**Create a WebSocket client**

Create a new Java class in your Android project, e.g., `WebSocketClient.java`. This class will establish a connection to your Spring Boot WebSocket backend:
```java
import org.java_websocket.client.WebSocketClient;
import org.java_websocket.drafts.Draft;
import org.java_websocket.handshake.ServerHandshake;
import org.java_websocket.protocols.Protocol;

import com.github.nkzawa.emitter.Emitter;
import com.github.nkzawa.socketio.client.IO;
import com.github.nkzawa.socketio.client.Socket;

import java.net.URI;
import java.net.URISyntaxException;

public class WebSocketClient {
