After installation, you need to link the library to your React Native project. Run:

```bash
npx react-native link react-native-camera
```

### Step 3: Configure the library (iOS)

For iOS, you need to add the `NSCameraUsageDescription` permission to your `Info.plist` file. You can do this manually or using the `react-native-config` library.

Manually, open your project in Xcode, navigate to the `Info` tab, and add a new key `NSCameraUsageDescription` with a string value that describes why your app needs camera access.

Alternatively, you can add the following lines to your `Info.plist` file:

```xml
<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
<string>This app needs camera access to take photos</string>
```

