Wistia is a popular video hosting platform, and integrating their uploader into an Angular 14 application can be a bit involved. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you get started:

**Prerequisites:**

1. Create a Wistia account and obtain an API token. You can find the API token in your Wistia account settings under "Account" > "API Tokens".
2. Install the `@wistia/upload` package using npm or yarn: `npm install @wistia/upload` or `yarn add @wistia/upload`

**Angular 14 Integration:**

1. Create a new Angular component for the uploader. For example, `wistia-uploader.component.ts` and `wistia-uploader.component.html`.
2. In the component, import the `WistiaUploader` class from the `@wistia/upload` package:
```typescript
import { Component, ElementRef } from '@angular/core';
import { WistiaUploader } from '@wistia/upload';
```
3. Create a reference to the `WistiaUploader` instance:
```typescript
export class WistiaUploaderComponent {
  uploader: WistiaUploader;
  constructor(private elementRef: ElementRef) { }
}
```
4. Initialize the `WistiaUploader` instance in the `ngAfterViewInit` lifecycle hook:
```typescript
ngAfterViewInit() {
  this.uploader = new WistiaUploader({
    accessToken: 'YOUR_API_TOKEN', // Replace with your Wistia API token
    projectId: 'YOUR_PROJECT_ID', // Replace with your Wistia project ID
    uploadOptions: {
      // Optional upload options
    }
  });
}
```
5. Create a container element in the component's template to render the uploader:
```html
<div #uploaderContainer></div>
```
6. Use the `uploader` instance to render the uploader in the container element:
```typescript
ngAfterViewInit() {
  //...
  this.uploader.render(this.elementRef.nativeElement.querySelector('#uploaderContainer'));
}
```
7. Handle upload events and errors using the `uploader` instance's event listeners:
```typescript
ngAfterViewInit() {
  //...
  this.uploader.on('upload:start', (file) => {
    console.log(`Upload started: ${file.name}`);
  });
  this.uploader.on('upload:progress', (file, progress) => {
    console.log(`Upload progress: ${file.name} - ${progress}%`);
  });
  this.uploader.on('upload:complete', (file) => {
    console.log(`Upload complete: ${file.name}`);
  });
  this.uploader.on('upload:error', (error) => {
    console.error(`Upload error: ${error.message}`);
  });
}
```
**Example Use Case:**

Here's a complete example of the `WistiaUploaderComponent`:
```typescript
import { Component, ElementRef } from '@angular/core';
import { WistiaUploader } from '@wistia/upload';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-wistia-uploader',
  template: `
    <div #uploaderContainer></div>
  `
})
export class WistiaUploaderComponent {
  uploader: WistiaUploader;
  constructor(private elementRef: ElementRef) { }

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    this.uploader = new WistiaUploader({
      accessToken: 'YOUR_API_TOKEN',
      projectId: 'YOUR_PROJECT_ID',
      uploadOptions: {
        // Optional upload options
      }
    });
    this.uploader.render(this.elementRef.nativeElement.querySelector('#uploaderContainer'));
    this.uploader.on('upload:start', (file) => {
      console.log(`Upload started: ${file.name}`);
    });
    this.uploader.on('upload:progress', (file, progress) => {
      console.log(`Upload progress: ${file.name} - ${progress}%`);
    });
    this.uploader.on('upload:complete', (file) => {
      console.log(`Upload complete: ${file.name}`);
    });
    this.uploader.on('upload:error', (error) => {
      console.error(`Upload error: ${error.message}`);
    });
  }
}
```
Remember to replace `YOUR_API_TOKEN` and `YOUR_PROJECT_ID` with your actual Wistia API token and project ID.

