**Step 1: Create a new directory for your extension and create the following files:**

* `manifest.json`: This file contains metadata about your extension, such as its name, description, and permissions.
* `contentScript.js`: This script will be injected into web pages and will be responsible for finding and linking Tezos addresses.
* `popup.html` and `popup.js`: These files are optional and can be used to create a popup that allows users to configure the extension or view additional information.

**Step 2: Define the manifest file (manifest.json)**

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 2,
  "name": "Tezos Address Linker",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Links Tezos wallet and contract addresses to tzkt.io",
  "content_scripts": [
    {
      "matches": ["<all_urls>"],
      "js": ["contentScript.js"]
    }
  ],
  "permissions": ["activeTab"]
}
```

**Step 3: Write the content script (contentScript.js)**

This script will use regular expressions to find Tezos addresses on the page and replace them with links to tzkt.io.

```javascript
function linkTezosAddresses() {
  // Regular expression to match Tezos addresses
  const tezosAddressRegex = /\b([tz][1-9A-HJ-NP-Za-km-z]{33})\b/g;

  // Find all text elements on the page
  const textElements = document.querySelectorAll('text, span, p, div');

  // Loop through each text element
  textElements.forEach((element) => {
    // Get the text content of the element
    const text = element.textContent;

    // Check if the text contains a Tezos address
    if (tezosAddressRegex.test(text)) {
      // Replace the Tezos address with a link to tzkt.io
      const linkedText = text.replace(tezosAddressRegex, (match) => {
        return `<a href="https://tzkt.io/${match}" target="_blank">${match}</a>`;
